h timestamps.\n184-\n185-### `cloche list`\n--\n195-| `--all` | Show all runs, not just the last hour. |\n196-\n197:Columns: run ID, workflow name, type (`host` or `container`), title (truncated to 40 characters), state, container ID (if running), error message (if failed).\n198-\n199-### `cloche logs`\n--\n223-```\n224-\n225:Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure or if the container\n226-dies unexpectedly.\n227-\n--\n234-```\n235-\n236:### `cloche delete`\n237-\n238:Delete a retained Docker container. Accepts either a Docker container name/ID\n239-or a Cloche run ID. If given a run ID, the daemon looks up the associated\n240:container.\n241-\n242-```\n243:cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n244-```\n245-\n--\n344-\n345-Files in `.cloche/overrides/` are copied on top of `/workspace/` in the\n346:container. Use this for container-specific configuration:\n347-\n348-```\n349-.cloche/overrides/\n350:  CLAUDE.md              # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (replaces host version)\n351-```\n352-\n353:### 5. Make sure your project builds in the container\n354-\n355-The default Dockerfile generated by `cloche init` uses `cloche-base:latest` as its\n--\n487-```\n488-\n489:Or at the workflow level via a `container` block:\n490-\n491-```\n492-workflow \"develop\" {\n493:  container {\n494-    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n495-  }\n--\n501-\n502-Priority (highest to lowest): step-level `agent_command`, workflow-level\n503:`container { agent_command }`, `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var, default (`claude`).\n504-\n505-### Agent Fallback Chains\n--\n554-my-project/\n555-├── .cloche/\n556:│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow definition\n557-│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n558:│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image\n559-│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration (orchestration, evolution)\n560-│   ├── prompts/\n--\n564-│   ├── scripts/\n565-│   │   └── prepare-prompt.sh # Host-side prompt generation script\n566:│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n567:│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n568-│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n569-│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt (from --prompt flag)\n--\n586-| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address (unix socket or TCP) |\n587-| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n588:| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` (container) or `local` (subprocess, for dev) |\n589-| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n590-| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | — | HTTP address for the web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n591-| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | (auto-detected) | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n592-| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | — | Command for LLM calls — evolution and merge conflict resolution (e.g. `claude`) |\n593:| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | — | Passed into Docker containers |\n594:| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | — | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n595-| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | — | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n596-","numLines":149}}
