ENT_PATH` | (auto-detected) | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n592-| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | — | Command for LLM calls — evolution and merge conflict resolution (e.g. `claude`) |\n593-| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | — | Passed into Docker containers |\n594-| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | — | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n595-| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | — | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n--\n597-### Client Configuration\n598-\n599-| Variable | Default | Description |\n600-|----------|---------|-------------|\n601-| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon address (gRPC) |\n602:| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address (web dashboard, `cloche logs --follow`) |\n603-\n604-## Build Commands\n605-\n606-```\n607-make build          # Build all binaries to bin/"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"50dccf18-98cd-411d-b917-3226e2ea14f2","uuid":"3c4b443e-f8b0-4167-a3b7-8ac6220d3c3b","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"36-manages Docker containers, tracks run state in SQLite, and handles\n37-container cleanup. Containers are automatically removed after successful\n38-runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their\n39-container for debugging.\n40-\n41:To enable the web dashboard, set `CLOCHE_HTTP` (e.g.\n42:`CLOCHE_HTTP=:8080 bin/cloched`). The dashboard is not started unless\n43-this variable is set.\n44-\n45-### 3. Run a workflow\n46-\n47-From your project directory (must be inside a git repository):\n--\n158-\n159-| Flag | Description |\n160-|------|-------------|\n161-| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche` in the project directory. |\n162-| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` and injected into agent steps. |\n163:| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary of the work being done. Displayed in `cloche status`, `cloche list`, and the web dashboard. If omitted, the agent 